Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and heat broiler to high or oven to 500 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Trim and slice @zucchini{1}(trimmed and sliced into ½-inch-thick rounds). Pick @oregano{¼}(leaves picked from stems, stems discarded, and leaves roughly chopped).

Place zucchini on a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}. Season with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and @Italian seasoning{½%tsp} (1 tsp for 4 servings; you'll use more later). Broil or bake on top rack until browned and softened, ~{5-7%minutes}.

> TIP: Watch carefully to avoid burning.

Remove #baking sheet{} from oven; adjust temperature to 450 degrees.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add @Italian chicken sausage mix{9}(broken into pieces) and half the oregano. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until sausage is browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat.

Meanwhile, place @flatbreads{2} on a second lightly oiled baking sheet. Toast in oven until lightly browned, ~{5-7%minutes}.

> For 4 servings, divide flatbreads between 2 sheets; swap rack positions halfway through baking.

Spread half the @Colavita crushed tomatoes{13.76%oz can} in a thin layer on toasted flatbreads (use all the crushed tomatoes for 4 servings). Season with salt, pepper, and @Italian seasoning{½%tsp} (1 tsp for 4; use the rest as you like). Evenly top with sausage, zucchini, and @mozzarella{½%cup}.

Bake flatbreads until edges are golden brown and cheese has melted, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Sprinkle flatbreads with as much remaining oregano as you like. Slice into pieces and serve with @vegetable oil{2%tbsp} on the side.